B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                 FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
FY 2026 Plans:
- Accelerated interoperability with Joint mission partners by preparing for the United States Navy's Consolidated Afloat Networks
and Enterprise Services (USN CANES) Surface Environment testing and USN adoption, enabling interoperability with United
States Marine Corps (USMC) and implementing software and infrastructure integrations with Army Battlefield Coordination
Detachment (BCD).
- Supported updates and modernization to the Common Operational Picture used by the USAF and COCOMs with integration of
C2Core Air, Global Command and Control System - Joint (GCCS-J), and Maven Smart System.
-Initiated advanced Major Theater War (MTW) interoperability with coalition partners by beginning coordination of command and
control (C2) analysis/roadmap alignment of modernized systems and cloud interoperability with Five Eyes (FVEY) nations though
interoperability with FVEY networks as well as AOC WS support in FVEY environments to meet COCOM and USAF requirements.
- Delivered AppTX to the Air Operations Center (AOC) enterprise as the cloud-based Air Operations Center Weapon System
(AOC WS) to add flexibility and resiliency to operational C2 by supporting distributed operations, maturing Primary Alternate
Contingency and Emergency Planning (PACE planning), increasing real-time system monitoring and streamlining capability
delivery.
- Implemented commercial and DoW common data layers (CDLs) to eliminate manual transfer of data, eliminate labor-intensive
logic workflows and build data foundation to take advantage of artificial intelligence (AI); enable modernized Dynamic Targeting
(DT) through accelerating the collection and analysis of data in periphery systems; leveraging a common operating picture (COP)
for global situational awareness between commands.
- Established the AOC enterprise dedicated experimentation platform enabling rapid onboarding and technical validation of
systems to quickly determine their ability to meet warfighter outcomes and enable decision advantage.
- Accelerated the Air Tasking Cycle (ATC) by integrating C2 systems that drive Master Air Attack Plan (MAAP) automation and
rapidly integrate data sources to enable dynamic mission replanning (DMR).
- Provided a robust 24x7x365 operational support framework for the AOC software and infrastructure, encompassing proactive
monitoring, incident response, performance tuning, and preventative maintenance, guaranteeing enterprise-grade reliability,
scalability, and security as it integrates across the AOC infrastructure.
-Continued to leverage software engineering capacity to align with the strategic roadmap & software initial capabilities document
priorities, which includes expanding access to mission partners to support Denied, Disrupted, Intermittent, and Limited bandwidth
scenarios; achieving Deliberate Planning Major Theater War capabilities/capacity across the AOC enterprise; conducting
functional AOC, Joint and mission partner assessments; defining architecture and deployment of; and continuing investment in
dynamic targeting and streamlined workflows.
- Continued to transition from legacy applications/systems such as Theater Battle Management Core Systems Force Level
