FY 2027 Plans:
For FY 2027, funds will evolve the AOC Decision Advantage (ADA). The primary objective is to mature the data-centric AOC
WS by delivering advanced integration and automation capabilities. These efforts are essential for achieving decision advantage
and operational superiority in a highly contested environment, directly supporting critical CJADC2 objectives for Major Theater
War (MTW) operations. This program will transition from initial capability development to providing advanced, dynamic decision
support for the warfighter. ADA is executing the following integrated Lines of Effort (LOEs):
- Advanced Data Integration. This LOE will focus on enhancing data interoperability to enable advanced task automation. Building
on initial FY 2026 data standardization, the program will integrate Tactical Command and Control (TAC C2) data into the Maven
Smart System (MSS) platform, enriching the common operational picture with authoritative C2 information. A key deliverable
for this fiscal year is the development of a C2 ontology, which will create a machine-readable structure to dramatically increase
interoperability and enable automated reasoning across disparate data sources.
- Automation of the Air Tasking Cycle. The program will deliver the next tranche of automation capabilities. Work will focus on
providing advanced plan generation and visualization tools to give commanders and planners clearer, more intuitive situational
awareness. Furthermore, the program will develop integrated Mission Report (MISREP) and Tactical Report (TACREP) analysis,
automating the ingestion and analysis of mission reports to accelerate the assessment phase of the targeting cycle and provide
near real-time feedback into the ATC.
- Dynamic Mission Replanning (DMR). This LOE will mature the Dynamic Mission Replanning (DMR) capability from initial
development into a functional decision support tool. The program will leverage advanced algorithms and collaborative tools within
MSS to provide warfighters with rapid, data-driven recommendations for in-flight mission adjustments. By integrating real-time
data feeds with the newly developed C2 ontology, the system will be able to propose optimized solutions for rerouting assets,
reassigning targets, and responding to emerging threats.
- Warfighter Training and System Adoption. To ensure the effective employment of these advanced capabilities, the program
will continue the strategic deployment of Palantir Field Service Representatives (FSRs). In FY 2027, FSR focus will shift to
providing advanced training on DMR and automated analysis tools. Additionally, access will be expanded to include partner
forces, enhancing coalition interoperability and supporting distributed operations.
