 AF DCGS Software Acquisition Pathway (SWP) - Mission Applications (MAS), Mission Data Services (MDS) and Operations, Integration and Transformation (OI&T):
 Delivers mission-critical, end-user software applications required for analysts'' global orchestration, sense-making, tailored analysis (battlespace awareness, battlespace
 characterization, and targetable custody) and data dissemination of a multitude of sensor data via Mission Applications, Mission Data Services, and Operations
 Integration & Transformation sections. The Software Acquisition Pathway (SWP) rapidly develops, integrates, tests, evaluates and fields new and updated GEOINT,
 SIGINT, & Multi-INT capabilities by leveraging COTS/GOTS Software when available, enables quick/seamless integration of new sensors, data types, sensor planning,
 and C2 capabilities; and provides data link visualization capabilities on to AF DCGS resilient, distributed architecture (private on-premises and/or commercial cloud
 environments) to meet mission assured requirements. Breakout of categories under Software Acquisition Pathway are included below:

 A. Mission Applications

 Mission Applications - GEOINT: efforts include development and integration of sensor C2, planning, and management; mission management; GEOINT High-Altitude
 (HA) and Full Motion Video (FMV) processing, exploitation and workflow capabilities; and product dissemination to support DCGS analysts' global orchestration, sense-
 making, tailored analysis (battlespace awareness, battlespace characterization, and targetable custody) and integration and dissemination of a multitude of sensor data
 tasks, as well as IC/DoD cyber security and Zero Trust mandates.

 Mission Applications - SIGINT: efforts include development and integration of sensor C2, planning, and management; mission management; sensor data emulator;
 SIGINT processing, exploitation and workflow capabilities; and product dissemination to support DCGS analysts' global orchestration, sense-making, tailored analysis
 (battlespace awareness, battlespace characterization, and targetable custody) and integration of a multitude of sensor data tasks, as well as IC/DoD cyber security and
 Zero Trust mandates.


 B. Mission Data Services

 Multi-INT Data Services: efforts include development and integration of new and modernization of, shared data services to include voice and chat communications,
 collaboration, and situational awareness; Multi-INT tailored analytic capabilities; enterprise services, cross domain solutions, enterprise service bus data exchange and
 interoperability capabilities, ArcGIS common production environment/disposition of forces initiatives as well as IC/DoD cyber security and Zero Trust mandates.

 C. Ops Integration and Transformation

 Includes management and funding for AF DCGS Dev/Sec/Ops Continuous Integration/Continuous Delivery (CI/CD) environment and agile software development, test,
 integration and deployment activities. CI/CD leverages both commercial cloud and on premises infrastructure. Funds and manages program office test and evaluation
 activities and Enterprise Cloud Test Environment. Manages PMO Cyber and Zero Trust efforts.

 This program element included all necessary expenses required to manage, execute, and deliver weapon system capability. The use of such program funds would be in
 addition to the civilian pay expenses budgeted in program elements 0605829F, 0605831F, 0605833F, and 0605898F.


