A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The Small Business Technology Transfer (STTR) program requires Federal agency that has an extramural budget for Research and Development (R&D) in excess
of $100,000,000 to set aside 0.45% for STTR. This funds cooperative R&D between small businesses and research institutions. The goal of the STTR program is to
facilitate the transfer of technology developed by a research institution through the entrepreneurship of a small business concern.

