This program falls within the SDA mission area which provides a ground-based radar system that detects, tracks, and maintains custody of deep space objects 24/7 in
all weather and through the solar exclusion gap. DARC will augment the Space Surveillance Network as an additional sensor with increased capacity and capability for
deep space object custody, providing full global coverage.

