Description: SDA includes effective identification, characterization, and understanding of any factor, passive or active, associated
with the space domain.

Performs space-based SDA analysis, research, and development for the SILENTBARKER system in partnership with the NRO.

FY 2026 Plans:
Mandatory (reconciliation) funding in FY2026 will continue advancing space-based SDA capabilities critical to operations in the
contested space domain, with a focus on system resiliency, prototyping, and operational experimentation.

Key planned efforts include:

SILENTBARKER Expansion: Continue launch preparations, integration, and development activities for the SILENTBARKER
Expansion increment, as well as development for the follow-on SILENTBARKER-B increment to enhance GEO-based SDA
capabilities. Support ongoing mission data processing and dissemination efforts across SILENTBARKER and other SDA
prototypes. Technology Development and Prototyping: Advance SDA capability through technology enhancements targeting
evolving threats. FY2026 efforts will include studies, SB-NEXT studies, analyses, demonstrations, and experimentation to support
future upgrades, system extensions, and performance augmentations for surveillance and reconnaissance. Oculus Hosted
Payload Program: Continue development and integration of SDA Hosted Payload on a commercial platform. FY 2026 will integrate
the Oculus payload onto a host, including payload characterization and environmental testing. The Oculus effort remains a cost-
effective GEO-based SDA gap-filler leveraging commercial and international partnerships. Prototype Missions (Oracle-M): Launch,
on-orbit experimentation, and operations for AFRL and SSC prototype missions. Enterprise Integration and Resiliency: Continue
support for implementing resilient SDA systems and enhancing situational awareness. Activities may include program office
support, technical studies, experimentation, integration and testing of C2 systems, mission partner interfaces, space test/ combat
range events, and related support efforts. Strategic Partnerships: FY 2026 will further leverage commercial, international, and
interagency collaboration opportunities to expand SDA capabilities and accelerate threat-responsive innovation.
FY 2027 Plans:
Key planned efforts include:

SILENTBARKER-B: Continue development for the next increment of GEO-based SDA capabilities.


