D. Acquisition Strategy
The SILENTBARKER Acquisition Strategy was approved to minimize the SDA Space Based surveillance gap. SILENTBARKER Baseline launched in FY 2023. The
SBSS Follow-on (SBSS FO) Materiel Development Decision was approved by the Milestone Decision Authority (MDA) on April 5, 2016. The Acquisition Strategy
Panel was completed with the MDA on August 29, 2016. To satisfy the SDA architecture needs, the SBSS FO program requirements combined with an NRO program
and were updated in the December 2017 SILENTBARKER Statement of Capabilities. The USSF is partnered with the NRO on SILENTBARKER space segment and
telemetry, tracking, and commanding (TT&C) program segments to further National Security Space objectives. Mutual investment for the non- recurring engineering
(NRE) cost enables the potential lower unit costs and increase satellite capacity. The SILENTBARKER phased acquisition approach is executed in accordance with
NRO approved acquisition strategy and signed agreements between the USSF and NRO. The agreement includes the SILENTBARKER Baseline program and its
follow-on increments, SILENTBARKER Expansion and SILENTBARKER-B. The SILENTBARKER Expansion contract was awarded Jun 2021 to extend capabilities past


