B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                     FY 2025     FY 2026       FY 2027
Title: Global Sensor Watch (GSW)                                                                                                           40.005      53.067        39.247
Description: GSW provides an integrated Space Domain Awareness (SDA) architecture to deliver a resilient, high capacity,
sensitive, timely, and comprehensive global ground and space-based network of sensors that cover the geocentric and cislunar
orbital regimes. GSW is a resilient, automated cross-sensor tip and cue capability that provides overlapping, assured, and viable
surveillance options for executing event response, and SDA data processing at multiple classification levels. To ensure the
successful implementation of a resilient, overlapping, assured, and viable architecture, GSW includes the necessary sensor
communication upgrades to ensure data transport/throughput, compatibility, and effects-based tactical tasking/response
functionality. This is accomplished by utilizing machine-to-machine (M2M) autonomy and artificial intelligence/machine learning
(AI/ML) and other emerging technologies. GSW enables highly available, non-stovepiped sensor planning, tasking, response, and
data collection, as well as processed information/products/results to be stored, shared, and integrated for warfighting and analysis.

FY 2026 Plans:
Complete investments in GSW Sensor Communication Upgrades (SCU) and Missile Defense Agency (MDA) integration for the
remaining assets and capabilities, in support of the USSPACECOM funded Project Lighthouse (LH1 & LH2) including:
-Complete investment for integration of radar sites: Eglin Radar, 2 Upgraded Early Warning Radars (UEWR), Millstone Radar Site
Massachusetts; and Reagan Test Site assets (Space Fence, Millimeter Wave (MMW) Radar, ARPA Lincoln C-Band Observables
Radar (ALCOR), Haystack Ultrawideband Satellite Imaging Radar (HUSIR), and the Haystack Auxiliary (HAX) Radar with other
characterization and operational intelligence capabilities.
-Complete Ground Based Radar-Kwajalein radome work and sensor array development.
-Continue efforts toward 5 sites: DARC Site 1, COBRA DANE, GEODSS, Ascension, and REDLAN, as sites are available.
-Vet new SDA capability deliveries and concepts of operations for optimizing legacy SDA sensor operations via other
USSPACECOM operations and test activities.
-Expand to additional SSN sites, mesh network for essential SCU communications and resilient data transport capability.
-Expand deployment of Al-prototype MACHINA integration with commercial, allied, and DoW SDA capabilities for automated
sensor orchestration and integration with operational C2 (Space C2, Integrated Sensor Support Services (IS3), MDA, etc).
-Mature prototyping and initial operationalization of Optical Cued Radar Search (OCRS) and automated radar imagery exposure
and exploitation, tracked as part of the USSPACECOM "Zulu Wookie” needs.

-Continue tip-and-cue software and launch custody and high-rate revisit capabilities at Millimeter Wave (MMW) Radar, ARPA
Lincoln C-Band Observables Radar (ALCOR), Haystack Ultrawideband Satellite Imaging Radar (HUSIR), Haystack Auxiliary
(HAX) and ALTAIR radars.

Continue Global Sensor Watch (GSW) efforts including:

