This project develops strategies and technologies to reduce musculoskeletal injury (MSKI) rates and improve outcomes following Return to Duty (RTD) in the Army
training, operational, and medical communities to improve Soldier readiness.

The cited research is fully coordinated with PE 0602143A (Soldier Lethality Technology) and complimentary to PE 0603118A (Soldier Lethality Advanced Technology)
and is fully coordinated with the Army Training and Doctrine Command (TRADOC) and other Services in order to avoid duplication of effort.

